                                <p>According to the  
  NTA (National Testing Agency), there are three parameters that students must meet: education qualifications, age limits and booking criteria. Therefore, candidates must pass the 12th exam with at least 50% points in physics, chemistry, biology and English subjects. Candidates in the SC / ST / OBC category must achieve at least 40% of points to qualify for NEET 2023, and candidates must be at least 17 years old at admission after clearing NEET. In addition, the upper limit of age in the general category is 25 years old, and in the case of ST / ST / OBC & PWD, it is exempted up to 30 years old. 

                                
 
	</p>
                              
